title: Graham Greene Novels and Short Stories (23 Books)
description:
Graham Greene was an English novelist, short story writer, playwright, screenplay writer, travel writer and critic whose works explore the ambivalent moral and political issues of the modern world. Greene combined serious literary acclaim with wide popularity. Many of his espionage thrillers were made into movies, and he wrote the screenplay for The Third Man starring Orson Welles.
